        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—On some of those who were thus restrained the effect may well have been that they were roused to a higher life and did turn from “vanities” to the living God. We must, at any rate, think of St. Paul’s work at Lystra as lasting long enough to allow time for the foundation of a church there. Among the more conspicuous converts were the devout Jewesses, Lois and her daughter Eunice (more accurately, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Eunike",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")",
        "children": []
