      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the young Timotheus (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Timothy 1:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). No mention is made of his father, and Eunice may have been a widow; but the fact that the boy had grown up uncircumcised rather suggests the influence of a living father. (See Note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
